  7class CoreTest(unittest.TestCase):
  8    """
  9    Provides useful methods for the use in tests.
 10    """
 11
 12    @staticmethod
 13    def are_floats_equal(f1: float, f2: float, tolerance: float = 10 ** (-10)) -> float:
 14        """
 15        Compares two floats for equality with respect to a tolerance.
 16
 17        Parameters
 18        ----------
 19        f1: float
 20            First float for the comparison
 21        f2: float
 22            Second float for the comparison
 23        tolerance: float
 24            Max. difference between the floats to consider them equal
 25
 26        Returns
 27        -------
 28        True
 29            If the floats are equal
 30        """
 31        return abs(f1 - f2) < tolerance
 32
 33    @staticmethod
 34    def get_default_value(arg_name: str, model=FMT20.CoreModel) -> float:
 35        """
 36        Returns the default value of a parameters of specific model.
 37
 38        Parameters
 39        ----------
 40        arg_name: str
 41            Name of the parameter
 42        model
 43            Type of the model to get the default value from
 44
 45        Returns
 46        -------
 47        float
 48            Default value of the parameter
 49        """
 50        args_name = model.__init__.__code__.co_varnames[1:]  # "self" is not needed
 51        default_value = model.__init__.__defaults__
 52        arg_index = args_name.index(f"{arg_name}")
 53        return default_value[arg_index]
 54
 55    def get_welfare_value(
 56        self,
 57        market_situation: Literal["duopoly", "with_innovation", "without_innovation"],
 58        model=FMT20.CoreModel,
 59    ) -> float:
 60        """
 61        Calculates the default value of welfare for a specific model and market situation.
 62
 63        Market situations:
 64        - duopoly
 65        - monopoly with innovation
 66        - monopoly without innovation
 67
 68        Parameters
 69        ----------
 70        market_situation: Literal["duopoly", "with_innovation", "without_innovation"]
 71            To calculate the total welfare for
 72        model
 73            Type of the model to get the default value from
 74
 75        Returns
 76        -------
 77        float
 78            Default value of the total welfare
 79        """
 80        consumer_surplus = CoreTest.get_default_value(
 81            f"consumer_surplus_{market_situation}", model
 82        )
 83        incumbent_profit = CoreTest.get_default_value(
 84            f"incumbent_profit_{market_situation}", model
 85        )
 86        try:
 87            # handle case of duopoly
 88            startup_profit = CoreTest.get_default_value(
 89                f"startup_profit_{market_situation}", model
 90            )
 91        except ValueError:
 92            startup_profit = 0
 93        return consumer_surplus + incumbent_profit + startup_profit

 96class TestCoreModel(CoreTest):
 97    """
 98    Provides methods for model setup and tests valid setup of model.
 99    """
100
101    def setupModel(self, **kwargs) -> None:
102        """
103        Sets up a model for a test.
104
105        The type of the model is corresponding to the testcase.
106
107        Parameters
108        ----------
109        **kwargs
110            Parameter values for the model
111        """
112        self.model = FMT20.CoreModel(**kwargs)
113
114    def setUpConfiguration(
115        self, config_id: int, merger_policy=FMT20.MergerPolicies.Strict, **kwargs
116    ) -> None:
117        """
118        Sets up a model from a preset configuration.
119
120        Parameters
121        ----------
122        config_id: int
123            ID of the preset configuration
124        merger_policy: FMT20.MergerPolicies
125            Merger policy to set in the model.
126        **kwargs
127            Parameter values for the model
128        """
129        config = FMT20.LoadParameters(config_id)
130        config.adjust_parameters(**kwargs)
131        config.params.merger_policy = merger_policy
132        self.setupModel(**config())
133
134    def test_valid_setup_default_values(self):
135        self.setupModel()
136
137    def test_uniform_distribution(self):
138        self.setupModel(
139            asset_distribution=FMT20.Distributions.UniformDistribution,
140            standard_distribution=False,
141        )
142        self.assertEqual(
143            1,
144            self.model.asset_distribution.cumulative(
145                self.model.development_costs, **self.model.asset_distribution_kwargs
146            ),
147        )

155    def setUp(self) -> None:
156        self.model_type = self.get_model_type()
157        self.model = self.model_type()

159    @staticmethod
160    def get_model_type():
161        return FMT20.MergerPolicy
162
163    def abstract_property_test(
164        self, property_, property_name: str, invalid_value=120
165    ) -> None:
166        """
167        Skeleton for all tests of model properties.
168
169        Example
170        --------
171        ```
172        model = FMT20.OptimalMergerPolicy()
173        self.abstract_property_test(model_type.startup_assets, "startup_assets")
174        ```
175
176        Parameters
177        ----------
178        property_
179            Property of the model
180        property_name: str
181            Name of the property as a string
182        invalid_value: int
183            Invalid value for the property
184        """
185        value = self.get_default_value(property_name)
186        self._test_get(property_, value)
187        self._test_valid_set(property_, value)
188        self._test_invalid_set(property_, invalid_value)
189
190    def _test_get(self, property_, value):
191        self.assertTrue(self.are_floats_equal(value, property_.fget(self.model)))
192
193    def _test_invalid_set(self, property_, invalid_value):
194        self.assertRaises(
195            AssertionError, lambda: property_.fset(self.model, invalid_value)
196        )
197
198    def _test_valid_set(self, property_, value):
199        value += 0.01
200        property_.fset(self.model, value)
201        self.assertTrue(self.are_floats_equal(value, value, property_.fget(self.model)))

class CoreTest(unittest.case.TestCase): 
 8class CoreTest(unittest.TestCase):
 9    """
10    Provides useful methods for the use in tests.
11    """
12
13    @staticmethod
14    def are_floats_equal(f1: float, f2: float, tolerance: float = 10 ** (-10)) -> float:
15        """
16        Compares two floats for equality with respect to a tolerance.
17
18        Parameters
19        ----------
20        f1: float
21            First float for the comparison
22        f2: float
23            Second float for the comparison
24        tolerance: float
25            Max. difference between the floats to consider them equal
26
27        Returns
28        -------
29        True
30            If the floats are equal
31        """
32        return abs(f1 - f2) < tolerance
33
34    @staticmethod
35    def get_default_value(arg_name: str, model=FMT20.CoreModel) -> float:
36        """
37        Returns the default value of a parameters of specific model.
38
39        Parameters
40        ----------
41        arg_name: str
42            Name of the parameter
43        model
44            Type of the model to get the default value from
45
46        Returns
47        -------
48        float
49            Default value of the parameter
50        """
51        args_name = model.__init__.__code__.co_varnames[1:]  # "self" is not needed
52        default_value = model.__init__.__defaults__
53        arg_index = args_name.index(f"{arg_name}")
54        return default_value[arg_index]
55
56    def get_welfare_value(
57        self,
58        market_situation: Literal["duopoly", "with_innovation", "without_innovation"],
59        model=FMT20.CoreModel,
60    ) -> float:
61        """
62        Calculates the default value of welfare for a specific model and market situation.
63
64        Market situations:
65        - duopoly
66        - monopoly with innovation
67        - monopoly without innovation
68
69        Parameters
70        ----------
71        market_situation: Literal["duopoly", "with_innovation", "without_innovation"]
72            To calculate the total welfare for
73        model
74            Type of the model to get the default value from
75
76        Returns
77        -------
78        float
79            Default value of the total welfare
80        """
81        consumer_surplus = CoreTest.get_default_value(
82            f"consumer_surplus_{market_situation}", model
83        )
84        incumbent_profit = CoreTest.get_default_value(
85            f"incumbent_profit_{market_situation}", model
86        )
87        try:
88            # handle case of duopoly
89            startup_profit = CoreTest.get_default_value(
90                f"startup_profit_{market_situation}", model
91            )
92        except ValueError:
93            startup_profit = 0
94        return consumer_surplus + incumbent_profit + startup_profit

def get_welfare_value( self, market_situation: Literal['duopoly', 'with_innovation', 'without_innovation'], model=Fumagalli_Motta_Tarantino_2020.Models.Base.CoreModel'>) -> float: 
56    def get_welfare_value(
57        self,
58        market_situation: Literal["duopoly", "with_innovation", "without_innovation"],
59        model=FMT20.CoreModel,
60    ) -> float:
61        """
62        Calculates the default value of welfare for a specific model and market situation.
63
64        Market situations:
65        - duopoly
66        - monopoly with innovation
67        - monopoly without innovation
68
69        Parameters
70        ----------
71        market_situation: Literal["duopoly", "with_innovation", "without_innovation"]
72            To calculate the total welfare for
73        model
74            Type of the model to get the default value from
75
76        Returns
77        -------
78        float
79            Default value of the total welfare
80        """
81        consumer_surplus = CoreTest.get_default_value(
82            f"consumer_surplus_{market_situation}", model
83        )
84        incumbent_profit = CoreTest.get_default_value(
85            f"incumbent_profit_{market_situation}", model
86        )
87        try:
88            # handle case of duopoly
89            startup_profit = CoreTest.get_default_value(
90                f"startup_profit_{market_situation}", model
91            )
92        except ValueError:
93            startup_profit = 0
94        return consumer_surplus + incumbent_profit + startup_profit
